  34,8,"Has he fabricated a lie against God or is he insane?‚ÄĚ In fact, those who do not believe in the Hereafter are bound for torment and have strayed farthest ňĻfrom the truthňļ"
  34,9,"Have they not then seen all that surrounds them of the heavens and the earth? If We willed, We could cause the earth to swallow them up, or cause ňĻdeadlyňļ pieces of the sky to fall upon them. Surely in this is a sign for every servant who turns ňĻto Godňļ"
  34,10,"Indeed, We granted David a ňĻgreatňļ privilege from Us, ňĻcommanding:ňļ ‚ÄúO mountains! Echo his hymns! And the birds as well.‚ÄĚ We made iron mouldable for him"
  34,11,"instructing: ‚ÄúMake full-length armour, ňĻperfectlyňļ balancing the links. And work righteousness ňĻO family of David!ňļ. Indeed, I am All-Seeing of what you do.‚ÄĚ"
  34,12,"And to Solomon ňĻWe subjectedňļ the wind: its morning stride was a month‚Äôs journey and so was its evening stride. And We caused a stream of molten copper to flow for him, and ňĻWe subjectedňļ some of the jinn to work under him by his Lord‚Äôs Will. And whoever of them deviated from Our command, We made them taste the torment of the blaze"
  34,13,"They made for him whatever he desired of sanctuaries, statues,¬†basins as large as reservoirs, and cooking pots fixed ňĻinto the groundňļ. ňĻWe ordered:ňļ ‚ÄúWork gratefully, O family of David!‚ÄĚ ňĻOnlyňļ a few of My servants are ňĻtrulyňļ grateful"
  34,14,"When We decreed Solomon‚Äôs death, nothing indicated to the ňĻsubjectedňļ jinn that he was dead except the termites eating away his staff.¬†So when he collapsed, the jinn realized that if they had ňĻreallyňļ known the unseen, they would not have remained in ňĻsuchňļ humiliating servitude"
